                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" id="arsenicandoldlace_sng_1" hclass="sense"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">a humorous US play (1941) by Joseph Kasselring. The story is about two old women who murder their visitors. It had 1 444 performances on Broadway and a film version was made in 1944. It is still regularly performed by <span class="ndv" tofix="" xt="ndv" href="amateur_topg_1">amateur</span> actors, especially in Britain.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
